Phylogenetic tree of the 
   Streptomyces isolates from the Laohu Ditch and their nearest relatives based on 16S rDNA sequences. The inner ring indicates the relationship of the 
   Streptomyces spp., Cluster 1 in shade of red, Cluster 2 in shade of yellow, Cluster 3 in shade of blue, Cluster 4 in shade of green, Cluster 5 in shade of orange, Cluster 6 in shade of lavender, Cluster 7 in shade of skyblue, Cluster 8 in shade of pink, Cluster 9 in shade of brown, Cluster 10 in shade of cyan; the black semi-ring and the light blue semi-ring represent Group I and GroupII, respectively; the middle ring indicates the distribution of the 73 isolates in near-root soils of 15 plant communities. 
